German for young people between 16 and 21
Young adults between the ages of 16 and 21 who do not yet speak German well and still have to go to school can attend the "Vocational Integration Class" (BIK;
Berufsintegrationsklasse) at the State Vocational Training Centre (BSZ;
Staatliches Berufliches Schulzentrum) in Neusäß.
For young people who cannot yet read and write (well), there are "Intensive Language Classes" (SIK;
Sprachintensivklassen).
You can get information directly from the BSZ.
State Vocational School Centre Neusäß
Landrat-Dr.
sekretariat@bszneusaess.de
